               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of al-Ṣahīfah al-Kāmilah by Zayn al-ʻĀbidīn ʻAlī ibn al-Ḥusayn, d. 710?
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="CODRINGTON.READE_NO_4_1_BOX_3-item1">
                     <author key="person_81971228" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/81971228/">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Zayn al-ʻĀbidīn ʻAlī ibn al-Ḥusayn, d. 710?</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">زين العابدين علي بن الحسين</persName>
                     </author>
                     <note>Legendary attribution. The reputed author is the fourth Imam of the Shi'ites.</note>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_47">al-Ṣahīfah al-Kāmilah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_47">الصحيفة الكاملة</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="work_47">A Collection of 54 prayers, with an extra prayer for the last hour of Friday</title>
                     <note>Bound with Nos 4 (1B), 4 (2), 4 (3), 4 (4) Bound upside down. .</note>
                     <incipit>Haddathana al-saiyid al-ajall Najm al-Din Baha' al-Sharaf Muhammad</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Not in Morley Printed Cat. Arabic. (Not Persian) But placed by Morley in the section Persian Theology. Under his number 30 Morley has a final item, a fragment of a prayer book by Khwaja Nasir Tusi, but this is not with this MS at present (2007).</bibl>
                        <bibl>Otto Loth, A Catalogue of the Arabic Manuscripts in the Library of the India Office, No 334, pp. 3-5.</bibl>
                        <bibl>GAS, i, pp. 526-7.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
